46int nv04_dac_output_offset(struct drm_encoder *encoder)
47{
48 struct dcb_output *dcb = nouveau_encoder(encoder)->dcb;
49 int offset = 0;
50
51 if (dcb->or & (8 | DCB_OUTPUT_C))
52 offset += 0x68;
53 if (dcb->or & (8 | DCB_OUTPUT_B))
54 offset += 0x2000;
55
56 return offset;
57}
58
59/*
60 * arbitrary limit to number of sense oscillations tolerated in one sample
61 * period (observed to be at least 13 in "nvidia")
62 */
63#define MAX_HBLANK_OSC 20
64
65/*
66 * arbitrary limit to number of conflicting sample pairs to tolerate at a
67 * voltage step (observed to be at least 5 in "nvidia")
68 */
69#define MAX_SAMPLE_PAIRS 10
70
71static int sample_load_twice(struct drm_device *dev, bool sense[2])
72{
73 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
74 struct nvif_object *device = &drm->device.object;
75 int i;
76
77 for (i = 0; i < 2; i++) {
78 bool sense_a, sense_b, sense_b_prime;
79 int j = 0;
80
81 /*
82 * wait for bit 0 clear -- out of hblank -- (say reg value 0x4),
83 * then wait for transition 0x4->0x5->0x4: enter hblank, leave
84 * hblank again
85 * use a 10ms timeout (guards against crtc being inactive, in
86 * which case blank state would never change)
87 */
88 if (nvif_msec(&drm->device, 10,
89 if (!(nvif_rd32(device, NV_PRMCIO_INP0__COLOR) & 1))
90 break;
91 ) < 0)
92 return -EBUSY;
93
94 if (nvif_msec(&drm->device, 10,
95 if ( (nvif_rd32(device, NV_PRMCIO_INP0__COLOR) & 1))
96 break;
97 ) < 0)
98 return -EBUSY;
99
100 if (nvif_msec(&drm->device, 10,
101 if (!(nvif_rd32(device, NV_PRMCIO_INP0__COLOR) & 1))
102 break;
103 ) < 0)
104 return -EBUSY;
105
106 udelay(100);
107 /* when level triggers, sense is _LO_ */
108 sense_a = nvif_rd08(device, NV_PRMCIO_INP0) & 0x10;
109
110 /* take another reading until it agrees with sense_a... */
111 do {
112 udelay(100);
113 sense_b = nvif_rd08(device, NV_PRMCIO_INP0) & 0x10;
114 if (sense_a != sense_b) {
115 sense_b_prime =
116 nvif_rd08(device, NV_PRMCIO_INP0) & 0x10;
117 if (sense_b == sense_b_prime) {
118 /* ... unless two consecutive subsequent
119 * samples agree; sense_a is replaced */
120 sense_a = sense_b;
121 /* force mis-match so we loop */
122 sense_b = !sense_a;
123 }
124 }
125 } while ((sense_a != sense_b) && ++j < MAX_HBLANK_OSC);
126
127 if (j == MAX_HBLANK_OSC)
128 /* with so much oscillation, default to sense:LO */
129 sense[i] = false;
130 else
131 sense[i] = sense_a;
132 }
133
134 return 0;
135}
136
137static enum drm_connector_status nv04_dac_detect(struct drm_encoder *encoder,
138 struct drm_connector *connector)
139{
140 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->dev;
141 struct nvif_object *device = &nouveau_drm(dev)->device.object;
142 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
143 uint8_t saved_seq1, saved_pi, saved_rpc1, saved_cr_mode;
144 uint8_t saved_palette0[3], saved_palette_mask;
145 uint32_t saved_rtest_ctrl, saved_rgen_ctrl;
146 int i;
147 uint8_t blue;
148 bool sense = true;
149
150 /*
151 * for this detection to work, there needs to be a mode set up on the
152 * CRTC. this is presumed to be the case
153 */
154
155 if (nv_two_heads(dev))
156 /* only implemented for head A for now */
157 NVSetOwner(dev, 0);
158
159 saved_cr_mode = NVReadVgaCrtc(dev, 0, NV_CIO_CR_MODE_INDEX);
160 NVWriteVgaCrtc(dev, 0, NV_CIO_CR_MODE_INDEX, saved_cr_mode | 0x80);
161
162 saved_seq1 = NVReadVgaSeq(dev, 0, NV_VIO_SR_CLOCK_INDEX);
163 NVWriteVgaSeq(dev, 0, NV_VIO_SR_CLOCK_INDEX, saved_seq1 & ~0x20);
164
165 saved_rtest_ctrl = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_TEST_CONTROL);
166 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_TEST_CONTROL,
167 saved_rtest_ctrl & ~NV_PRAMDAC_TEST_CONTROL_PWRDWN_DAC_OFF);
168
169 msleep(10);
170
171 saved_pi = NVReadVgaCrtc(dev, 0, NV_CIO_CRE_PIXEL_INDEX);
172 NVWriteVgaCrtc(dev, 0, NV_CIO_CRE_PIXEL_INDEX,
173 saved_pi & ~(0x80 | MASK(NV_CIO_CRE_PIXEL_FORMAT)));
174 saved_rpc1 = NVReadVgaCrtc(dev, 0, NV_CIO_CRE_RPC1_INDEX);
175 NVWriteVgaCrtc(dev, 0, NV_CIO_CRE_RPC1_INDEX, saved_rpc1 & ~0xc0);
176
177 nvif_wr08(device, NV_PRMDIO_READ_MODE_ADDRESS, 0x0);
178 for (i = 0; i < 3; i++)
179 saved_palette0[i] = nvif_rd08(device, NV_PRMDIO_PALETTE_DATA);
180 saved_palette_mask = nvif_rd08(device, NV_PRMDIO_PIXEL_MASK);
181 nvif_wr08(device, NV_PRMDIO_PIXEL_MASK, 0);
182
183 saved_rgen_ctrl = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_GENERAL_CONTROL);
184 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_GENERAL_CONTROL,
185 (saved_rgen_ctrl & ~(NV_PRAMDAC_GENERAL_CONTROL_BPC_8BITS |
186 NV_PRAMDAC_GENERAL_CONTROL_TERMINATION_75OHM)) |
187 NV_PRAMDAC_GENERAL_CONTROL_PIXMIX_ON);
188
189 blue = 8; /* start of test range */
190
191 do {
192 bool sense_pair[2];
193
194 nvif_wr08(device, NV_PRMDIO_WRITE_MODE_ADDRESS, 0);
195 nvif_wr08(device, NV_PRMDIO_PALETTE_DATA, 0);
196 nvif_wr08(device, NV_PRMDIO_PALETTE_DATA, 0);
197 /* testing blue won't find monochrome monitors. I don't care */
198 nvif_wr08(device, NV_PRMDIO_PALETTE_DATA, blue);
199
200 i = 0;
201 /* take sample pairs until both samples in the pair agree */
202 do {
203 if (sample_load_twice(dev, sense_pair))
204 goto out;
205 } while ((sense_pair[0] != sense_pair[1]) &&
206 ++i < MAX_SAMPLE_PAIRS);
207
208 if (i == MAX_SAMPLE_PAIRS)
209 /* too much oscillation defaults to LO */
210 sense = false;
211 else
212 sense = sense_pair[0];
213
214 /*
215 * if sense goes LO before blue ramps to 0x18, monitor is not connected.
216 * ergo, if blue gets to 0x18, monitor must be connected
217 */
218 } while (++blue < 0x18 && sense);
219
220out:
221 nvif_wr08(device, NV_PRMDIO_PIXEL_MASK, saved_palette_mask);
222 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_GENERAL_CONTROL, saved_rgen_ctrl);
223 nvif_wr08(device, NV_PRMDIO_WRITE_MODE_ADDRESS, 0);
224 for (i = 0; i < 3; i++)
225 nvif_wr08(device, NV_PRMDIO_PALETTE_DATA, saved_palette0[i]);
226 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_TEST_CONTROL, saved_rtest_ctrl);
227 NVWriteVgaCrtc(dev, 0, NV_CIO_CRE_PIXEL_INDEX, saved_pi);
228 NVWriteVgaCrtc(dev, 0, NV_CIO_CRE_RPC1_INDEX, saved_rpc1);
229 NVWriteVgaSeq(dev, 0, NV_VIO_SR_CLOCK_INDEX, saved_seq1);
230 NVWriteVgaCrtc(dev, 0, NV_CIO_CR_MODE_INDEX, saved_cr_mode);
231
232 if (blue == 0x18) {
233 NV_DEBUG(drm, "Load detected on head A\n");
234 return connector_status_connected;
235 }
236
237 return connector_status_disconnected;
238}
239
240uint32_t nv17_dac_sample_load(struct drm_encoder *encoder)
241{
242 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->dev;
243 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
244 struct nvif_object *device = &nouveau_drm(dev)->device.object;
245 struct nvkm_gpio *gpio = nvxx_gpio(&drm->device);
246 struct dcb_output *dcb = nouveau_encoder(encoder)->dcb;
247 uint32_t sample, testval, regoffset = nv04_dac_output_offset(encoder);
248 uint32_t saved_powerctrl_2 = 0, saved_powerctrl_4 = 0, saved_routput,
249 saved_rtest_ctrl, saved_gpio0 = 0, saved_gpio1 = 0, temp, routput;
250 int head;
251
252#define RGB_TEST_DATA(r, g, b) (r << 0 | g << 10 | b << 20)
253 if (dcb->type == DCB_OUTPUT_TV) {
254 testval = RGB_TEST_DATA(0xa0, 0xa0, 0xa0);
255
256 if (drm->vbios.tvdactestval)
257 testval = drm->vbios.tvdactestval;
258 } else {
259 testval = RGB_TEST_DATA(0x140, 0x140, 0x140); /* 0x94050140 */
260
261 if (drm->vbios.dactestval)
262 testval = drm->vbios.dactestval;
263 }
264
265 saved_rtest_ctrl = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_TEST_CONTROL + regoffset);
266 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_TEST_CONTROL + regoffset,
267 saved_rtest_ctrl & ~NV_PRAMDAC_TEST_CONTROL_PWRDWN_DAC_OFF);
268
269 saved_powerctrl_2 = nvif_rd32(device, NV_PBUS_POWERCTRL_2);
270
271 nvif_wr32(device, NV_PBUS_POWERCTRL_2, saved_powerctrl_2 & 0xd7ffffff);
272 if (regoffset == 0x68) {
273 saved_powerctrl_4 = nvif_rd32(device, NV_PBUS_POWERCTRL_4);
274 nvif_wr32(device, NV_PBUS_POWERCTRL_4, saved_powerctrl_4 & 0xffffffcf);
275 }
276
277 if (gpio) {
278 saved_gpio1 = nvkm_gpio_get(gpio, 0, DCB_GPIO_TVDAC1, 0xff);
279 saved_gpio0 = nvkm_gpio_get(gpio, 0, DCB_GPIO_TVDAC0, 0xff);
280 nvkm_gpio_set(gpio, 0, DCB_GPIO_TVDAC1, 0xff, dcb->type == DCB_OUTPUT_TV);
281 nvkm_gpio_set(gpio, 0, DCB_GPIO_TVDAC0, 0xff, dcb->type == DCB_OUTPUT_TV);
282 }
283
284 msleep(4);
285
286 saved_routput = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_DACCLK + regoffset);
287 head = (saved_routput & 0x100) >> 8;
288
289 /* if there's a spare crtc, using it will minimise flicker */
290 if (!(NVReadVgaCrtc(dev, head, NV_CIO_CRE_RPC1_INDEX) & 0xC0))
291 head ^= 1;
292
293 /* nv driver and nv31 use 0xfffffeee, nv34 and 6600 use 0xfffffece */
294 routput = (saved_routput & 0xfffffece) | head << 8;
295
296 if (drm->device.info.family >= NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_CURIE) {
297 if (dcb->type == DCB_OUTPUT_TV)
298 routput |= 0x1a << 16;
299 else
300 routput &= ~(0x1a << 16);
301 }
302
303 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_DACCLK + regoffset, routput);
304 msleep(1);
305
306 temp = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_DACCLK + regoffset);
307 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_DACCLK + regoffset, temp | 1);
308
309 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_TESTPOINT_DATA,
310 NV_PRAMDAC_TESTPOINT_DATA_NOTBLANK | testval);
311 temp = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_TEST_CONTROL);
312 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_TEST_CONTROL,
313 temp | NV_PRAMDAC_TEST_CONTROL_TP_INS_EN_ASSERTED);
314 msleep(5);
315
316 sample = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_TEST_CONTROL + regoffset);
317 /* do it again just in case it's a residual current */
318 sample &= NVReadRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_TEST_CONTROL + regoffset);
319
320 temp = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_TEST_CONTROL);
321 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_TEST_CONTROL,
322 temp & ~NV_PRAMDAC_TEST_CONTROL_TP_INS_EN_ASSERTED);
323 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_TESTPOINT_DATA, 0);
324
325 /* bios does something more complex for restoring, but I think this is good enough */
326 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_DACCLK + regoffset, saved_routput);
327 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_TEST_CONTROL + regoffset, saved_rtest_ctrl);
328 if (regoffset == 0x68)
329 nvif_wr32(device, NV_PBUS_POWERCTRL_4, saved_powerctrl_4);
330 nvif_wr32(device, NV_PBUS_POWERCTRL_2, saved_powerctrl_2);
331
332 if (gpio) {
333 nvkm_gpio_set(gpio, 0, DCB_GPIO_TVDAC1, 0xff, saved_gpio1);
334 nvkm_gpio_set(gpio, 0, DCB_GPIO_TVDAC0, 0xff, saved_gpio0);
335 }
336
337 return sample;
338}
339
340static enum drm_connector_status
341nv17_dac_detect(struct drm_encoder *encoder, struct drm_connector *connector)
342{
343 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(encoder->dev);
344 struct dcb_output *dcb = nouveau_encoder(encoder)->dcb;
345
346 if (nv04_dac_in_use(encoder))
347 return connector_status_disconnected;
348
349 if (nv17_dac_sample_load(encoder) &
350 NV_PRAMDAC_TEST_CONTROL_SENSEB_ALLHI) {
351 NV_DEBUG(drm, "Load detected on output %c\n",
352 '@' + ffs(dcb->or));
353 return connector_status_connected;
354 } else {
355 return connector_status_disconnected;
356 }
357}
358
359static bool nv04_dac_mode_fixup(struct drm_encoder *encoder,
360 const struct drm_display_mode *mode,
361 struct drm_display_mode *adjusted_mode)
362{
363 if (nv04_dac_in_use(encoder))
364 return false;
365
366 return true;
367}
368
369static void nv04_dac_prepare(struct drm_encoder *encoder)
370{
371 const struct drm_encoder_helper_funcs *helper = encoder->helper_private;
372 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->dev;
373 int head = nouveau_crtc(encoder->crtc)->index;
374
375 helper->dpms(encoder, DRM_MODE_DPMS_OFF);
376
377 nv04_dfp_disable(dev, head);
378}
379
380static void nv04_dac_mode_set(struct drm_encoder *encoder,
381 struct drm_display_mode *mode,
382 struct drm_display_mode *adjusted_mode)
383{
384 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->dev;
385 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
386 int head = nouveau_crtc(encoder->crtc)->index;
387
388 if (nv_gf4_disp_arch(dev)) {
389 struct drm_encoder *rebind;
390 uint32_t dac_offset = nv04_dac_output_offset(encoder);
391 uint32_t otherdac;
392
393 /* bit 16-19 are bits that are set on some G70 cards,
394 * but don't seem to have much effect */
395 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_DACCLK + dac_offset,
396 head << 8 | NV_PRAMDAC_DACCLK_SEL_DACCLK);
397 /* force any other vga encoders to bind to the other crtc */
398 list_for_each_entry(rebind, &dev->mode_config.encoder_list, head) {
399 if (rebind == encoder
400 || nouveau_encoder(rebind)->dcb->type != DCB_OUTPUT_ANALOG)
401 continue;
402
403 dac_offset = nv04_dac_output_offset(rebind);
404 otherdac = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_DACCLK + dac_offset);
405 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_DACCLK + dac_offset,
406 (otherdac & ~0x0100) | (head ^ 1) << 8);
407 }
408 }
409
410 /* This could use refinement for flatpanels, but it should work this way */
411 if (drm->device.info.chipset < 0x44)
412 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_TEST_CONTROL + nv04_dac_output_offset(encoder), 0xf0000000);
413 else
414 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_TEST_CONTROL + nv04_dac_output_offset(encoder), 0x00100000);
415}
416
417static void nv04_dac_commit(struct drm_encoder *encoder)
418{
419 struct nouveau_encoder *nv_encoder = nouveau_encoder(encoder);
420 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(encoder->dev);
421 struct nouveau_crtc *nv_crtc = nouveau_crtc(encoder->crtc);
422 const struct drm_encoder_helper_funcs *helper = encoder->helper_private;
423
424 helper->dpms(encoder, DRM_MODE_DPMS_ON);
425
426 NV_DEBUG(drm, "Output %s is running on CRTC %d using output %c\n",
427 nouveau_encoder_connector_get(nv_encoder)->base.name,
428 nv_crtc->index, '@' + ffs(nv_encoder->dcb->or));
429}
430
431void nv04_dac_update_dacclk(struct drm_encoder *encoder, bool enable)
432{
433 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->dev;
434 struct dcb_output *dcb = nouveau_encoder(encoder)->dcb;
435
436 if (nv_gf4_disp_arch(dev)) {
437 uint32_t *dac_users = &nv04_display(dev)->dac_users[ffs(dcb->or) - 1];
438 int dacclk_off = NV_PRAMDAC_DACCLK + nv04_dac_output_offset(encoder);
439 uint32_t dacclk = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, 0, dacclk_off);
440
441 if (enable) {
442 *dac_users |= 1 << dcb->index;
443 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, 0, dacclk_off, dacclk | NV_PRAMDAC_DACCLK_SEL_DACCLK);
444
445 } else {
446 *dac_users &= ~(1 << dcb->index);
447 if (!*dac_users)
448 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, 0, dacclk_off,
449 dacclk & ~NV_PRAMDAC_DACCLK_SEL_DACCLK);
450 }
451 }
452}
453
454/* Check if the DAC corresponding to 'encoder' is being used by
455 * someone else. */
456bool nv04_dac_in_use(struct drm_encoder *encoder)
457{
458 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->dev;
459 struct dcb_output *dcb = nouveau_encoder(encoder)->dcb;
460
461 return nv_gf4_disp_arch(encoder->dev) &&
462 (nv04_display(dev)->dac_users[ffs(dcb->or) - 1] & ~(1 << dcb->index));
463}
464
465static void nv04_dac_dpms(struct drm_encoder *encoder, int mode)
466{
467 struct nouveau_encoder *nv_encoder = nouveau_encoder(encoder);
468 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(encoder->dev);
469
470 if (nv_encoder->last_dpms == mode)
471 return;
472 nv_encoder->last_dpms = mode;
473
474 NV_DEBUG(drm, "Setting dpms mode %d on vga encoder (output %d)\n",
475 mode, nv_encoder->dcb->index);
476
477 nv04_dac_update_dacclk(encoder, mode == DRM_MODE_DPMS_ON);
478}
479
480static void nv04_dac_save(struct drm_encoder *encoder)
481{
482 struct nouveau_encoder *nv_encoder = nouveau_encoder(encoder);
483 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->dev;
484
485 if (nv_gf4_disp_arch(dev))
486 nv_encoder->restore.output = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_DACCLK +
487 nv04_dac_output_offset(encoder));
488}
489
490static void nv04_dac_restore(struct drm_encoder *encoder)
491{
492 struct nouveau_encoder *nv_encoder = nouveau_encoder(encoder);
493 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->dev;
494
495 if (nv_gf4_disp_arch(dev))
496 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_DACCLK + nv04_dac_output_offset(encoder),
497 nv_encoder->restore.output);
498
499 nv_encoder->last_dpms = NV_DPMS_CLEARED;
500}
501
502static void nv04_dac_destroy(struct drm_encoder *encoder)
503{
504 struct nouveau_encoder *nv_encoder = nouveau_encoder(encoder);
505
506 drm_encoder_cleanup(encoder);
507 kfree(nv_encoder);
508}

510static const struct drm_encoder_helper_funcs nv04_dac_helper_funcs = {
511 .dpms = nv04_dac_dpms,
512 .save = nv04_dac_save,
513 .restore = nv04_dac_restore,
514 .mode_fixup = nv04_dac_mode_fixup,
515 .prepare = nv04_dac_prepare,
516 .commit = nv04_dac_commit,
517 .mode_set = nv04_dac_mode_set,
518 .detect = nv04_dac_detect
519};

521static const struct drm_encoder_helper_funcs nv17_dac_helper_funcs = {
522 .dpms = nv04_dac_dpms,
523 .save = nv04_dac_save,
524 .restore = nv04_dac_restore,
525 .mode_fixup = nv04_dac_mode_fixup,
526 .prepare = nv04_dac_prepare,
527 .commit = nv04_dac_commit,
528 .mode_set = nv04_dac_mode_set,
529 .detect = nv17_dac_detect
530};

532static const struct drm_encoder_funcs nv04_dac_funcs = {
533 .destroy = nv04_dac_destroy,
534};
535
536int
537nv04_dac_create(struct drm_connector *connector, struct dcb_output *entry)
538{
539 const struct drm_encoder_helper_funcs *helper;
540 struct nouveau_encoder *nv_encoder = NULL;
541 struct drm_device *dev = connector->dev;
542 struct drm_encoder *encoder;
543
544 nv_encoder = kzalloc(sizeof(*nv_encoder), GFP_KERNEL);
545 if (!nv_encoder)
546 return -ENOMEM;
547
548 encoder = to_drm_encoder(nv_encoder);
549
550 nv_encoder->dcb = entry;
551 nv_encoder->or = ffs(entry->or) - 1;
552
553 if (nv_gf4_disp_arch(dev))
554 helper = &nv17_dac_helper_funcs;
555 else
556 helper = &nv04_dac_helper_funcs;
557
558 drm_encoder_init(dev, encoder, &nv04_dac_funcs, DRM_MODE_ENCODER_DAC);
559 drm_encoder_helper_add(encoder, helper);
560
561 encoder->possible_crtcs = entry->heads;
562 encoder->possible_clones = 0;
563
564 drm_mode_connector_attach_encoder(connector, encoder);
565 return 0;
566}
